The crowd began massing in front of Rafik Hariri's mansion Wednesday as Lebanon prepared to bury him and the six bodyguards who were killed with him in a bomb blast.
The report, issued Thursday in the UN headquarters in New York, indicated that there was a " distinct lack of commitment " by Lebanese authorities to probe the crime, and the investigation was not carried out " in accordance with acceptable international standards . "
An independent, international investigation is need.
Lahoud called for finding the murders and who were behind the assassination.
